snippet: The first day of the 113th Congress brought a new diversity to the Capitol, including a record number of women and various firsts for the numbers of Latinos and Asians.
abstract: New 113th Congress includes record number of women, with 101 across both chambers, as well as various firsts for the number of Latinos and Asians; Senate has 20 women, and House has 81.

byline.contributor: Emmarie Huetteman, Ashley Southall and Jonathan Weisman contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The first day of the 113th Congress brought a new diversity to the Capitol, including a record number of women and various firsts for the numbers of Latinos and Asians.

headline.seo: First Day of 113th Congress Brings More Women to Capitol
headline.main: Day of Records and Firsts as 113th Congress Opens
